@realmoney @dougkass @SeabreezeLP Aug 02, 2022 | 02:30 PM EDT DOUG KASS My Positioning Observations in Last Week's Bloomberg Interview Again, for emphasis, and as I discussed in my Bloomberg interview recently - the market is being buoyed by positioning of participants.

Here is what I previously said to Paul Sweeney and Tom Keene a few days back: To some degree this has been a position driven rally. Position usually doesn't fit in to my investment view but sometimes it does- especially in the extreme! Let me explain. 80% of market volume

is quantitative and passive trading. These products and strategies worship at the altar of price momentum. They know nothing about value but everything about price. The other 20% of market volume is active trading - mostly hedge funds. Thy are the marginal buyer. When price

momentum shifts to the upside, as it recently has, the 80% (quant strategies) follow and buy. That other 20%, hedge funds, have been defensively positioned (remember the BOFA bull/bear indicator has fallen to ZERO) and have been offsides as I noted when I turned more bullish

in our last interview about four weeks ago. Almost every smart hedge hogger I know has been bearish. Lets use Dan Loeb's Third Point as a proxy. Dan is the best of the best. In his investor letter he said he was over 70% net long at 2021 year end, 40% net long in April I beleive

and in June a bit over 20%. In the interim some have been forced to buy in this advance which has been virtually interrupted - hedge funds are the marginal buyer. We have witnessed the dual impact of both passive and active players buying over the last several weeks.
